com.tversity.airflinger.sdk.android
Interface Types.IEventCallback

Enclosing class:
Types
public static interface Types.IEventCallback

This interface defines callback functions that receive status change notifications.

Method Detail

OnPlayerStatusChange

void OnPlayerStatusChange(Player player,
                          Types.DeviceStatus previousStatus)
Invoked when a player status is changed.

Note: This callback will be invoked only if the EVENT_LISTEN_PLAYER_STATUS_CHANGE was specified in the call to AirFlinger.init

Parameters:
player - The player which has changed its status
previousStatus - The status the player was in, before this call

OnServerStatusChange

void OnServerStatusChange(Server server,
                          Types.DeviceStatus previousStatus)
Invoked when a server status is changed.

Note: This callback will be invoked only if the EVENT_LISTEN_SERVER_STATUS_CHANGE was specified in the call to AirFlinger.init

Parameters:
server - The server which has changed its status
previousStatus - The status the server was in, before this call

OnPlayerVolumeChange

void OnPlayerVolumeChange(Player player,
                          int volumeLevel)
Invoked when a player volume is changed.

Note 1: This callback will be invoked only if the EVENT_LISTEN_PLAYER_VOLUME_CHANGE was specified in the call to AirFlinger.init
Note 2: Devices that do not support volume change events will be periodically polled for their volume level

Parameters:
player - The player which has changed its status
volumeLevel - The current level of the player volume
